Currently, we create an external entity for an LDAP user when the user logs in or an admin views their account from the administration screen. This is the by product of fetching the propertyset in both of these instances. 

When an LDAP user logs in via SOAP however, no such fetching of the user's property set happens, so no external entity is created. 

We need to implement a more consistent and less accidental strategy for creating this external entity.

