Currently, confluence scans the user profile picture directory to find icons to display to the user when the user decides to select a profile picture.  Unfortunately, there is no ordering to this!  They end up in a random jumbled order.

My suggestion would be to order them by name - this way, if you wanted to group things (e.g., animals-frog, animals-horse, animals-snake or flags-australia, flags-canada, flags-uk, flags-usa, et al) you could do it by name, and have a decent presentation ordering to the user.  I had to remove my flags from the offering because they were scattered all over, and just made it a complete mess to pick images out.

A second note - consider more than four columns wide.

