I have created a modified create page action which pre-fills the editPermissionUser field so that forum posts (pages) can be automatically locked down to be only editable by the user who created the initial post (eg basic forum functionality) .. this works very well, however it requires me to include a modified createpage.vm, createpage-form.vm and page-permissions-form.vm (the first two are so that I can include my modified page-permissions-form)

The changes are very minor, and may be useful to other coders:

{code}
#tag (TextField "id=viewPermissionsGroups" "name='viewPermissionsGroups'" "theme='notable'")
#tag (TextField "id=viewPermissionsUsers" "name='viewPermissionsUsers'" "theme='notable'" )
#tag (TextField "id=editPermissionsGroups" "name='editPermissionsGroups'" "theme='notable'")
#tag (TextField "id=editPermissionsUsers" "name='editPermissionsUsers'" "theme='notable'" )
{code}

becomes

{code}
#tag (TextField "id=viewPermissionsGroups" "name='viewPermissionsGroups'" "theme='notable'" "value='$!viewPermissionsGroups'")
#tag (TextField "id=viewPermissionsUsers" "name='viewPermissionsUsers'" "theme='notable'" "value='$!viewPermissionsUsers'")
#tag (TextField "id=editPermissionsGroups" "name='editPermissionsGroups'" "theme='notable'" "value='$!editPermissionsGroups'")
#tag (TextField "id=editPermissionsUsers" "name='editPermissionsUsers'" "theme='notable'" "value='$!editPermissionsUsers'")
{code}

And that's it :D

I can keep going with the version I have since it does work, however it would be more 'correct' if this could be rolled into the main conf sourcebase and I could just re-use the original createpage.vm

